class Solution {
    public int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0) {
            int consumed = Math.min(mainTank, 5);
            mainTank -= consumed;
            distance += consumed * 10;
            if (consumed == 5 && additionalTank >= 1) {
                additionalTank -= 1;
                mainTank += 1;
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(mainTank / 5 + additionalTank)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the main tank's fuel, simulating fuel consumption and transfer from the additional tank when necessary, ensuring an efficient and accurate calculation of the maximum distance.

